  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for AMECEA 20th Plenary Assembly, 2022</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">After a long period of uncertainty caused by COVID 19 pandemic that affected the entire global movement and operations, AMECEA will be holding its 20th AMECEA plenary assembly that will take place in Dar es Salaam Tanzania from 9th &#x2013; 18th July 2022. The plenary will bring together bishops, representatives from other agents of evangelization and partners. The last AMECEA plenary assembly took place in Addis Abba in July 2018. 

The overall goal of the AMECEA 20th plenary assembly is to bring forth the awareness of the gravity of ecological crisis and enable the AMECEA region to embrace new habits in nurturing our common home. In order to achieve this goal, there is a need for concerted effort of various stakeholders.

General Objective: To conduct a study whereby the bishops will learn the gravity of ecological crisis and how it is affecting the life of the people in the region and deliberate on pertinent areas of action both pastoral and social aiming at slowing the pace of destruction.
Specific Objective: To conduct an effective 20th Plenary Assembly that will give room for a fruitful discussion during study session in order to address pastoral challenges on climate change.</narrative>
  </description>
